The paper focuses on pedestrian attribute recognition in video surveillance, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a flexible attribute localization module and a feature pyramid architecture, which are both related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve evaluating the proposed method on three pedestrian attribute datasets, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
